  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility package for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under VAD conditions. The package embeds weakener W-AR-05: the primary validation result for the Output Comparison factor references a well-documented experimental dataset by name in its narrative but omits the comparedAgainst link. The referenced dataset was collected under continuous-flow LVAD operating conditions at a fixed impeller speed of 3000 RPM, whereas the COU requires evaluation across five flow-speed combinations spanning 2400–3600 RPM. The overlapping operating point (3000 RPM, 5 L/min) creates superficial comparability, but the dataset does not capture the speed-dependent shear history that drives hemolysis prediction error at off-design points. The validation narrative discusses the comparator favourably without examining this scope mismatch, constituting an undercutting inference-method mismatch (D3).",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-predicts-absolute-hemolyis-class3-vad",
