      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version control, regression test suite coverage ≥ 90%, documented release notes for all physics modules used in hemolysis post-processing.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is used under a validated commercial license with documented regression testing. The Lagrangian hemolysis post-processor is a user-defined function developed in-house; its version control history is maintained in a private repository but formal regression tests cover only 6 of 11 identified code paths. Achieved level 3 falls short of the required level 4 for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated second-order spatial accuracy via MMS on rotating domain; iterative convergence to residual norm < 1e-5 for all simulations.",
      "rationale": "MMS test confirmed observed order 1.97, consistent with nominal second-order scheme. Iterative convergence criterion of 1e-6 was met. However, the MMS domain is a simplified annulus and does not exercise the impeller-volute interface or the sliding-mesh coupling used in the full pump model. A gap remains at the interface treatment level, limiting achieved level to 3."
