      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Evidence that simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing steps have been independently reviewed and that no systematic user errors are present.",
      "rationale": "No independent peer review of simulation setup was performed. Model inputs and boundary conditions were set by the primary analyst without documented second-party verification. Flagged as epistemic gap. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection and hemolysis damage accumulation model must be justified for the Reynolds number regime and shear stress magnitudes encountered at all COU operating points; alternative model forms must be considered.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model is used with the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation. Justification for SST k-ω is provided at the nominal operating point based on prior literature. The power-law correlation is known to underestimate hemolysis at high shear rates (> 400 Pa) encountered near the impeller tip at 3600 RPM; this limitation is noted in a footnote but not addressed through model-form uncertainty quantification. No alternative turbulence or hemolysis model was evaluated. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
