      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (blood viscosity, RBC fragility parameters, power-law exponents) must be characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo UQ must propagate input uncertainty to nIH predictions at all five COU operating points.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed at the nominal operating point using Latin hypercube sampling (N=500) over blood viscosity, haematocrit, and power-law exponent distributions. Output uncertainty on nIH was ±18% at 95% confidence. UQ was not repeated at the four off-design operating points. The dependence of input sensitivity on impeller speed is uncharacterised. Achieved level 2."
